                                "byte_start": 81623,
                                "byte_stop": 99804,
                                "text": "...Freestone will be announced by Justice O\u2019Connor."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 4.525,
                        "stop": 253.832,
                        "byte_start": 99804,
                        "byte_stop": 0,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15092,
                            "name": "Sandra Day O\u0027Connor",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/sandra_day_oconnor",
                            "last_name": "O\u0027Connor",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2736,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 370242000,
                                    "date_end": 1138687200,
                                    "appointing_president": "Ronald Reagan",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2736"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32763,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 49563,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/sandra_day_oconnor.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 8894,
                            "identifier": "sandra_day_oconnor"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 4.525,
                                "stop": 10.752,
                                "byte_start": 99804,
                                "byte_stop": 124673,
                                "text": "This case comes here on writ of certiorari to the United States Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 10.752,
                                "stop": 18.861,
                                "byte_start": 124673,
                                "byte_stop": 157169,
                                "text": "Arizona has chosen to participate in a federally funded welfare program, Aid to Families with Dependent Children."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 18.861,
                                "stop": 38.424,
                                "byte_start": 157169,
                                "byte_stop": 235327,
                                "text": "As a condition of receiving that federal funding, a federal statute known as Title IV-D requires Arizona to help children and single parents obtain paternity determinations and child support orders and to collect support payments from absent parents."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 38.424,
                                "stop": 49.022,
                                "byte_start": 235327,
                                "byte_stop": 277750,
                                "text": "This lawsuit was brought by five single mothers living in Arizona whose children were not receiving child support from their absent fathers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 49.022,
                                "stop": 69.677,
                                "byte_start": 277750,
                                "byte_stop": 360402,
                                "text": "The mothers sued the Director of Arizona\u2019s Child Support Agency, claiming that the agency had not provided them with child support services, and that the State\u2019s failure were largely attributable to structural defects in the state agency; staff shortages, high case loads, and poor record keeping."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 69.677,
                                "stop": 88.652,
                                "byte_start": 360402,
                                "byte_stop": 436261,
                                "text": "They brought their lawsuit under 42 United States Code Section 1983 which imposes liability on anyone who under color  of state law, deprives the person of any rights, privileges, or immunity secured by the Constitution and laws of the United States."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.652,
                                "stop": 103.708,
                                "byte_start": 436261,
                                "byte_stop": 496552,
                                "text": "The mothers claimed that Title IV-D gave them rights and asked the court to order Arizona to achieve substantial compliance with federal law through all of its programmatic operations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 103.708,
                                "stop": 111.837,
                                "byte_start": 496552,
                                "byte_stop": 529048,
                                "text": "The District Court granted summary judgment for the Director but Court of Appeals for the Ninth Circuit reversed."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 111.837,
                                "stop": 136.362,
                                "byte_start": 529048,
                                "byte_stop": 627164,
                                "text": "It held that Title IV-D gave the mothers an individual right to have Arizona\u2019s Child Support Agency substantially comply with federal guidelines, and that the Secretary\u2019s authority to audit and cut funding of the agency did not foreclose an individual remedy for the plaintiffs under Section 1983."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 136.362,
                                "stop": 143.384,
                                "byte_start": 627164,
                                "byte_stop": 655167,
                                "text": "We disagree with the first portion of the Court of Appeals\u2019 analysis and therefore vacate the judgment."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 143.384,
                                "stop": 157.564,
                                "byte_start": 655167,
                                "byte_stop": 711905,
                                "text": "We disagree with the lower court\u2019s conclusion, the Ninth Circuit\u2019s conclusion, that individuals have a right to have Arizona\u2019s Child Support Agency substantially comply with Title IV-D."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 157.564,
                                "stop": 172.834,
                                "byte_start": 711905,
                                "byte_stop": 773032,
                                "text": "For a statute to create an enforceable right for individual plaintiffs that must be intended to benefit the plaintiff and must create judicially manageable standards and impose a binding obligation on the state."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 172.834,
                                "stop": 181.763,
                                "byte_start": 773032,
                                "byte_stop": 808767,
                                "text": "The requirement that a state be in substantial compliance, we think, is not intended to benefit particular individuals."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 181.763,
                                "stop": 191.237,
                                "byte_start": 808767,
                                "byte_stop": 846593,
                                "text": "The substantial compliance standard requires that a state must provide certain services only in a specified percentage of cases."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 191.237,
                                "stop": 206.49,
                                "byte_start": 846593,
                                "byte_stop": 907615,
                                "text": "For example, a state must collect over due support payments in 75% of state cases, and that numerical target is a system wide measure of performance triggering the Secretary\u2019s auditing and penalty provisions."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 206.49,
                                "stop": 213.118,
                                "byte_start": 907615,
                                "byte_stop": 934155,
                                "text": "It does not give particular individuals an enforceable right to receive child support services."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 213.118,
                                "stop": 223.264,
                                "byte_start": 934155,
                                "byte_stop": 974697,
                                "text": "We also think the Court of Appeals painted with too broad a brush in holding that Title IV-D created unspecified rights."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 223.264,
                                "stop": 231.456,
                                "byte_start": 974697,
                                "byte_stop": 1007507,
                                "text": "Our cases have always analyzed the plaintiffs\u0027 asserted right in their most concrete specific form."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 231.456,
                                "stop": 244.396,
                                "byte_start": 1007507,
                                "byte_stop": 1059230,
                                "text": "We send this case back to the District Court to construe the complaint in the first instance to determine exactly what right, considered in their most concrete specific form the mothers are asserting."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 244.396,
                                "stop": 246.39,
                                "byte_start": 1059230,
                                "byte_stop": 1067275,
                                "text": "The opinion is unanimous."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 246.39,
                                "stop": 253.832,
                                "byte_start": 1067275,
                                "byte_stop": 0,
                                "text": "Justice Scalia has filed a concurring opinion which is joined by Justice Kennedy."
                            }
                        ]
